subject: HISTORY
text: Give the century, B.C. or A.D., of each of the following, indicate who or what each was, and say why each is important in history: St. Augustine of Canterbury, Count Cavour, Thomas Cromwell, Earl of Essex, Hannibal, Lenin, Abraham Lincoln, Malcolm Canmore, Andrew Melville, the Massacre of Glencoe, the Battle of Lepanto, Charles Stewart Parnell, Pericles, the Treaty of Falaise, Jethro Tull.
